TopicTitle: Timewarp exhibiting weird behavior when boosting with solid rocket boosters and only solid rocket boosters

Articles.Content:
• KSP Version - v0.1.2.0
  • Operating System and version - Windows 11
  • CPU and GPU models, any other system information which could be relevant

CPU: Ryzen 9 7950x

GPU: Radeon 7900XT

  • Description of the bug.

Timewarp while boosting on a craft with only solid boosters causes multiple things to break.

 

  •  
    • Expected Behavior

                                 the craft should just continue boosting while timewarp is happening

    • Observed Behavior

                             while time warping while inside a sphere of influence will force the space craft into the planet that's being orbited at around 50x the speed of light

                             while time warping outside of a sphere of influence two things happen. either the game immediately crashes with the unity crash window or the game will destroy the craft

                            and then the light source in the Kerbol star will start to grow in size infinitely (effectively making a super nova effect) and then the game will crash

  • Steps to Replicate

                           create a craft whose engines are ONLY solid boosters, and time warp while those boosters are boosting

  • Fixes / Workarounds (if known..)
  • A list of ALL mods.  If the list is long, please consider using a spoiler window.
  • space-warp
  • lazy orbit
  • Shadow Utility LIB
  • Cheat Menu
  • No Seizure Warning
  • P.A.I.G.E-B-Gone
  • Other Notes / Screenshots / Log Files (if possible..)

I managed to catch a screen shot of the timewarp causing lights to act super weirdly, this screenshot is actually the shine on kerbin (this is without mods)

the mods shouldn't be changing anything about timewarp but I will test without the mods enabled
